  </oversight_info>
  <brief_summary>
    <textblock>
      This study wish to show if the preoperative level of pain, function or activity for hip and
      knee arthroplasty patients has any predictive value of the time it takes to fulfill the
      well-defined discharge criteria.
    </textblock>
  </brief_summary>
  <detailed_description>
    <textblock>
      The investigators would like to be able to identify those patients, for whom it will take
      longest time to fulfill the discharge criteria. With this knowledge the investigators will be
      able to initiate sufficient treatment already before operation.
    </textblock>
  </detailed_description>
